                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15657.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-05T14:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1915—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This morning General Villa handed me a message containing the following:</p>
                <p>The attack on Nogales by Carrancistas yesterday was a direct violation of
                    treaties signed by Maytorena and Calles through mediation of General Scott;
                    Maytorena has been compelled to withdraw troops from Yaqui Valley, placing in
                    jeopardy the lives of colonists in the valley; Villa declines any responsibility
                    for what might happen unless our Government forces Carrancistas to respect said
                    treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
